        {
            "_id": "oX5mS0nonoT9j23k",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Paint",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The blood painter has fresh blood applied to a claw using Dab.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The blood painter expends the blood on one claw to paint an illusion with the effects of one of the following spells: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Illusory Creature], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Illusory Disguise], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Illusory Object], or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Mirror Image].</p>\n<p>The Paint action gains the traits of the spell it's reproducing, and the blood painter can Sustain a Spell on these effects. They use a spell attack modifier of [[/r 1d20+20 #Spell Attack]]{+20} and DC 28 for these effects, which are heightened to 5th level.</p>\n<p>If they have fresh blood applied to two or more claws, the blood painter can expend the blood on all of them to instead produce the effects of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Cloak of Colors] or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Vibrant Pattern].</p>\n<p>Any effects produced by this ability have a +2 status bonus to attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and AC against the creature whose blood was used to Paint and that creature takes a -2 status penalty to Perception checks and saves against it.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
